propriate processes to manage the removal and reburial or cremation of human remains, and the removal and replacement of monuments to the deceased. Where remains are less than 100 years old, schedule 20 requires a notice to be published in the local newspaper and displayed at the burial ground. Relatives have the right to remove and re-inter or cremate the remains at the expense of the nominated undertaker, who must pay reasonable costs. I hope that provides some assurance to the hon. Gentleman that we are taking the issue seriously. Question put and agreed to. Clause 22 accordingly ordered to stand part of the Bill. Schedule 20 agreed to.     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     The Chair       Share       I propose revising my grouping, and that we debate clauses 23 to 42, and the associated schedules 21 to 31, together.     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Ms Ghani       Share       Ms Buck, may I take some direction? Are you proposing that I speak just to clause 23?     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     The Chair       Share       You may speak to any clause between clauses 23 and 42, and we will take the decisions at the end, rather than having a speech on each clause and making a decision on it, as we have been doing. This will allow you to make a speech on all of them together.     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Ms Ghani       Share       I understand. I will do my best, but do call me out if I get it wrong. Clause 23 Consecrated land Question proposed, That the clause st